sentence: carl clifford weber| carl clifford weber carl clifford weber, 77, of polo, mo died monday, june 8, 2015 at the shirkey nursing and rehabilitation center in richmond.
carl was born on june 27, 1937 in hardin, mo to william frank and pauline (blaker) weber.

survivors include four sons and two daughters-in-law, michael and shirley weber of richmond, mo, rodney weber of camden, mo, roger and donna weber of camden and stevie weber of richmond; two daughters and two sons-in-law, brenda and tom turner of richmond and millie and zane edelbrock of camden; one sister, mary geraldine hayes of milo, iowa; one aunt, lucille klingman of mexico, mo; 11 grandchildren; and 19 great-grandchildren also survive. in addition to his parents, carl was preceded in death by two brothers, ben weber and billy weber, who died in infancy; and two sisters, lena ruth lutz and marcella dye.
carl was a heavy equipment operator for everett quarries in plattsburg, mo for 25 years.
he was a former member of the i. o. o. f. lodge in richmond.
he was of the christian faith. he lived in ray county most of his life.
funeral services will be held on thursday, june 11, 2015 at 2:00 p. m. at the thurman funeral home in richmond.
visitation will be thursday, june 11, 2015 from 1:00 p. m. to 2:00 p. m. at thurman funeral home in richmond.
burial will be in the craven cemetery near camden.
on line condolences may be left on our website at www. thurmanfuneralhome.
